    feat: PureSecure CVE vulnerability database with DevSecOps CI/CD
    
    Build a professional CVE vulnerability details website powered by
    NVD API 2.0 with live data, search with autocomplete, and a full
    DevSecOps GitHub Actions pipeline.
    
    Frontend:
    - Homepage with latest CVEs feed (newest first)
    - Search page with autocomplete suggestions and severity filter
    - CVE detail page (CVSS scores, CWE mapping, affected products, references)
    - CWE detail page with associated CVEs
    - Clean professional design with green accent theme
    
    Backend:
    - FastAPI with async NVD API 2.0 client
    - SQLite caching layer with 24h TTL
    - Rate limiting (6s interval for NVD)
    - Built-in CWE reference dataset with live NVD fallback
    - Input validation and XSS prevention
    
    DevSecOps Pipeline (9 stages):
    - Lint (Flake8), SAST (Bandit), SCA (pip-audit + Safety)
    - Secret scanning (Gitleaks), SBOM (CycloneDX)
    - Unit tests (Pytest + coverage), Build, Deploy (GitHub Pages)
    - DAST (OWASP ZAP baseline scan)
    
